# Froglips — optional build-time environment.
#
# Everything here is OPTIONAL and NO-OP UNTIL SET. `npm run release` produces a
# working local (ad-hoc-signed) build with none of these. Set the Apple block to
# turn on Developer-ID signing + notarization so the build opens on a stranger's
# Mac WITHOUT the Gatekeeper "damaged/unverified" warning. Requires an Apple
# Developer account ($99/yr) + a "Developer ID Application" certificate.
#
# Copy to `.env`, fill in, and `source .env` (or export) before `npm run release`.
# `.env` is gitignored — never commit real credentials.

# ── Apple Developer ID signing + notarization (distribution builds) ──────────
# The Tauri bundler signs + notarizes + staples automatically when these are
# exported; release.sh detects APPLE_SIGNING_IDENTITY and the rest follows.
# APPLE_SIGNING_IDENTITY="Developer ID Application: YOUR NAME (TEAMID)"

# Certificate as base64 .p12 + its password (or rely on the login keychain):
# APPLE_CERTIFICATE="$(base64 -i DeveloperID.p12)"
# APPLE_CERTIFICATE_PASSWORD="<p12-password>"

# Notarization credentials — EITHER an app-specific password…
# APPLE_ID="you@apple.id"
# APPLE_PASSWORD="<app-specific-password>"
# APPLE_TEAM_ID="TEAMID"

# …OR an App Store Connect API key:
# APPLE_API_ISSUER="<issuer-uuid>"
# APPLE_API_KEY="<key-id>"
# APPLE_API_KEY_PATH="AuthKey_XXXXXXXXXX.p8"

# ── Updater signing (minisign) ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# The auto-updater verifies releases against the minisign pubkey embedded in
# tauri.conf.json. The PRIVATE key lives out-of-tree (default ~/.tauri/froglips.key,
# gitignored) — never put it here. Override its path/password only if needed:
# TAURI_SIGNING_PRIVATE_KEY="$(cat ~/.tauri/froglips.key)"
# TAURI_SIGNING_PRIVATE_KEY_PASSWORD="<key-password>"
#
# NOTE: the updater endpoint in tauri.conf.json points at GitHub Releases. While
# the repo is PRIVATE, unauthenticated update checks 404 — the in-app check fails
# silently (by design) until the release manifest (latest.json) + assets are
# served from a reachable location (a public releases mirror or GitHub Pages).
